    Modifier and Type Method Description
    protected void addVertices​(OctreeNode node, int skipEdge)
    Adds data (vertex, index, normal, texture) to the MeshData instance to make up a face with the given node The faces of all nodes connect to the chunk mesh Data is only added when the node contains part of the terrain, which means one of the voxel edges exhibits a sign change
    void createMesh​(BlockStorage storage, org.lwjgl.util.vector.Vector3f globalPosition, MeshData mesh)
    Creates the mesh via a dual contouring approach The data is stored in the passed mesh instance

    private double[] getSamples​(OctreeNode node)
    Queries the densities on the voxel origin and the "endpoint" of each axis
    protected org.lwjgl.util.vector.Vector3f roundToMinEdgeLength​(org.lwjgl.util.vector.Vector3f v)
    If MIN_EDGE_LENGTH will ever become less than 1 (so if the minimum block size is decreased) use this method to round the crossing position If MIN_EDGE_LENGTH is equal to 1 you could also just round the crossing position by converting the x, y, z- values to (int) or use Math.floor
    protected void triangulate​(OctreeNode node)

      protected org.lwjgl.util.vector.Vector3f roundToMinEdgeLength​(org.lwjgl.util.vector.Vector3f v)
      If MIN_EDGE_LENGTH will ever become less than 1 (so if the minimum block size is decreased) use this method to round the crossing position If MIN_EDGE_LENGTH is equal to 1 you could also just round the crossing position by converting the x, y, z- values to (int) or use Math.floor
